1826
01:26:45,820 --> 01:26:47,620
A black boy graduating
 from high school

1827
01:26:47,620 --> 01:26:53,080
in Lake City, South Carolina in
 the 50s was not a usual thing.

1828
01:26:53,080 --> 01:26:56,350
When I graduated from college,
 I rush back home, well,

1829
01:26:56,350 --> 01:26:58,910
my little brother was graduating
 from my same high school,

1830
01:26:58,910 --> 01:27:01,030
but that was not the
 reason I rushed home.

1831
01:27:01,030 --> 01:27:03,580
My grandmother was
 graduating too.

1832
01:27:06,180 --> 01:27:09,590
What did she think
 you should do next?

1833
01:27:09,590 --> 01:27:11,660
Well, she says I
 have too many degrees,

1834
01:27:11,660 --> 01:27:13,750
so I should decide for myself.

1835
01:27:13,750 --> 01:27:15,370
What do you do with
 all those degrees?

1836
01:27:15,370 --> 01:27:17,600
Well, I think after
 this mission is over,

1837
01:27:17,600 --> 01:27:21,890
I'm going to go back to
 South Carolina and teach.

1838
01:27:21,890 --> 01:27:24,800
Folks, we have a
 personal best here tonight.

1839
01:27:24,800 --> 01:27:27,320
Ron McNair is the most
 lucid guy at NASA.

1840
01:27:27,320 --> 01:27:29,000
When it comes to describing
 technical things,

1841
01:27:29,000 --> 01:27:31,060
he'll fascinate you.

1842
01:27:31,060 --> 01:27:32,980
I've never heard him talk
 so long about himself.

1843
01:27:36,130 --> 01:27:37,820
I think that's right JR.

1844
01:27:37,820 --> 01:27:38,520
Come on, now.

1845
01:27:38,520 --> 01:27:40,680
You've got to play this.

1846
01:27:40,680 --> 01:27:41,650
No.
 No.

1847
01:27:41,650 --> 01:27:42,420
No more for me.

1848
01:27:42,420 --> 01:27:43,620
As a matter of fact,
 we have a press

1849
