 us would go without her now.

1945
01:31:42,190 --> 01:31:43,890
Christa says
 she's not worried,

1946
01:31:43,890 --> 01:31:47,190
but fear might hit her when
 she starts to get on board.

1947
01:31:47,190 --> 01:31:50,610
What could you say to
 put her mind at ease?

1948
01:31:50,610 --> 01:31:51,810
I could tell her
 that she's right.

1949
01:31:54,660 --> 01:31:57,430
The unknown is
 mysterious, frightening.

1950
01:31:57,430 --> 01:31:59,640
When she walks out and she
 sees those giant boosters

1951
01:31:59,640 --> 01:32:04,050
and the big tank, 6 million
 pounds of fire and thunder

1952
01:32:04,050 --> 01:32:06,850
smoking, she'll know it's real.

1953
01:32:06,850 --> 01:32:08,940
Ron, I understand that
 you often visit schools

1954
01:32:08,940 --> 01:32:10,860
